FILED SENATE
Mar 25, 2025
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
S.B. 555
SESSION 2025
PRINCIPAL CLERK
S D
SENATE BILL DRS15210-MHa-72
Short Title: Wetlands Protection and Restoration Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Smith and Mayfield (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROTECT AND RESTORE WETLANDS IN NORTH CAROLINA.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4
5 PART I. FUNDING
6 SECTION 1.(a) Establishment and Purpose of Fund. – The sum of fifteen million
7 dollars ($15,000,000) in recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year is appropriated from the
8 General Fund to the Department of Environmental Quality. Funds appropriated by this section
9 shall be used by the Department to establish the Wetlands Restoration and Protection Fund
10 (Fund) as a special fund in the Department. The Fund consists of appropriations by the General
11 Assembly as well as contributions and grants from public or private sources. The purpose of the
12 Fund is to provide financial support for (i) wetland restoration projects, (ii) acquisition of
13 conservation easements, (iii) public awareness campaigns to educate citizens about the
14 importance of wetlands and the need for their protection and opportunities for volunteer wetlands
15 protection and restoration projects, through the Department's Office of Environmental Education
16 and Public Affairs, and (iv) enforcement of wetland protection laws as amended by Section 2 of
17 this act to restore protection of certain wetlands in the State that were removed from federal
18 protection under the Clean Water Act by the United States Supreme Court ruling in Sackett v.
19 EPA, 598 U.S. 651 (2023).
20 SECTION 1.(b) Reservation of Funds for Monitoring and Research. – Five million
21 dollars ($5,000,000) of the funds appropriated by subsection (a) of this section are designated for
22 wetland monitoring and research initiatives. The Department, in collaboration with relevant
23 stakeholders and research institutions, will conduct comprehensive monitoring and research to
24 assess the health and ecological value of wetlands throughout the State.
25 SECTION 1.(c) Report. – The Department shall submit a report no later than
26 September 1, 2026, and annually thereafter to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on
27 Agriculture and Natural and Economic Resources and the Fiscal Research Division on the
28 projects and activities funded by this act during the prior fiscal year. The Department shall
29 include in its initial report and may include in subsequent reports recommendations regarding
30 further legislative changes needed to provide comprehensive protection for isolated wetlands at
31 the State level in response to the Sackett decision. The reports shall also include, at a minimum,
32 the following:
33 (1) The beginning and ending balance of the Fund for the fiscal year.
34 (2) A listing of funding recipients, and the amount provided to each recipient.
35 (3) An overview of the use of funds by funding recipients, including a description
36 of projects constructed or planning milestones achieved.
